Title   : Urban Company among 3 IPOs to debut tomorrow. Which company could deliver the best listing pop? 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-16T05:01:14
Fetched : 2025-09-16T08:09:25.983638
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/ipos/fpos/urban-company-among-3-ipos-to-debut-tomorrow-which-company-could-deliver-the-best-listing-pop/articleshow/123914112.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Urban Company: The star attraction
Urban Company’s Rs 1,900 crore IPO was the most eagerly watched issue of the lot, and it did not disappoint. The offering was subscribed 103 times overall, with QIBs bidding 147 times, NIIs 77 times, and retail investors 41 times.
At the upper price band of Rs 103 per share, the issue was valued at rich multiples, yet its strong positioning as India’s largest tech-enabled home services platform gave confidence to institutional investors.
Urban Company’s GMP stands at 64%, the highest among the three listings. This indicates a potential listing price of around Rs 169 per share, suggesting healthy gains for those allotted shares.
Brokerages remain divided on valuations, but many recommend a “long-term hold” citing the company’s leadership in a fragmented market, brand recall, and expansion in geographies like the UAE and Singapore. Analysts caution that while near-term listing gains are likely, investors should weigh risks linked to profitability and scalability.
Shringar House of Mangalsutra: Niche jewellery play
Jewellery-focused Shringar House of Mangalsutra raised Rs 401 crore through its IPO priced at Rs 165 per share. The issue garnered bids worth over Rs 5124 crore, reflecting blockbuster demand. It was subscribed 60 times overall.
The company, which designs and manufactures mangalsutras in both domestic and overseas markets, has carved out a niche segment and counts leading jewellers like Titan, Malabar, and Joyalukkas among its clients.
Also Read: Urban Company GMP at nearly 70% on allotment day. Here's how you to check status
Its GMP is hovering around 19%, suggesting a modest listing price of Rs 196 per share. While the subscription was strong, analysts note that the jewellery segment has limited scalability compared to consumer tech platforms like Urban Company.
Still, Shringar’s consistent financial growth and strong B2B client base are things going for it.
Dev Accelerator: Co-working spaces play
Ahmedabad-based Dev Accelerator (DevX), a flexible office space provider, raised Rs 143 crore through its IPO at an issue price of Rs 61 per share. The company, which manages over 8.6 lakh sq ft of space across 28 centres, drew bids of nearly 64 times. The demand was strong from retail investors.
Despite the robust subscription, its GMP is just 13%, indicating a likely listing near Rs 69 per share. Analysts point out that while demand for managed offices is rising, the segment is highly competitive and cyclical. For investors, Dev Accelerator may offer steady but moderate returns compared to the other two issues.
Which IPO could deliver the best listing pop?
Based on GMP trends and subscription data, Urban Company is expected to deliver the strongest debut, potentially offering gains upwards of 40–50%. Shringar could deliver a respectable but modest pop of around 15–20%, while Dev Accelerator may see a more subdued listing despite strong oversubscription.
For investors, the choice may boil down to risk appetite: Urban Company for high-growth (but pricey) exposure, Shringar for niche jewellery play, and Dev Accelerator for a co-working story in the making.
(Disclaimer: Recommendations, suggestions, views and opinions given by the experts are their own. These do not represent the views of the Economic Times)
